
*** HOW TO INSTALL & USE DADY

(JL ALbarral, 20/10/2017)

> INTRODUCTION

dady is a program that allows users to control robotic nodes (amy, goon, willy, ...) through CLI.
It uses these libraries:
- the tron_talky lib for robotic language interpretation.
- the tron_comy lib for IPC communication.

usage: dady <talky message>

note: use dady without params to get the list of topics, categories and concepts available for communication.


> INSTALLATION


1. Download tron

git clone https://github.com/albarral/tron.git


2. Build dady project (in Netbeans)


3. Prepare to load required tron libs from everywhere:

touch tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/talky/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux > tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/comy/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux >> tron_dady.conf
echo /path_to_tron/tuly/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux >> tron_dady.conf
sudo mv tron_dady.conf /etc/ld.so.conf.d
sudo /sbin/ldconfig
(note: path_to_tron = tron installation path)


4. Prepare config files for tron logging:

see instructions in path_to_tron/logging/README_logging file
(note: path_to_tron = tron installation path)


5. Create link to dady executable in user's home folder:
 
cd
ln -s /path_to_tron/dady/dist/Debug/GNU-Linux/dady dady
(note: path_to_tron = tron installation path)



